<h1>Using the Age Map</h1>
<p>The Age Map is the core screen of AgeMap, displaying registered people visually sorted by age.</p>

<h2>Screen Layout</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Main area</strong> — A graph with people arranged by age. Older at the top, younger at the bottom</li>
  <li><strong>Top bar</strong> — Birthday reminder button and family tree mode toggle</li>
  <li><strong>Right panel</strong> — Group list with checkboxes to filter which groups are shown</li>
  <li><strong>Bottom</strong> — Add person button (+)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Gestures</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Pinch zoom</strong> — Zoom in/out with two fingers</li>
  <li><strong>Drag</strong> — Pan the view with one finger</li>
  <li><strong>Tap</strong> — Tap a person card to view details</li>
</ul>

<h2>Adding a Person</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Tap the <strong>+</strong> button at the bottom.</li>
  <li>Enter the name and date of birth.</li>
  <li>For lunar birthdays, toggle the lunar switch (auto-converted to solar).</li>
  <li>Select the groups they belong to.</li>
  <li>Optionally set a profile photo (camera or gallery).</li>
  <li>Tap save — they will be automatically placed on the age map.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Person Details</h2>
<p>Tap a person card on the age map to see their details at the bottom of the screen.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Precise age in years, months, and days</li>
  <li>Days until next birthday</li>
  <li>Zodiac sign, birthstone, and oriental zodiac</li>
  <li>Groups and family relationships</li>
</ul>

<h2>Setting "Me"</h2>
<p>Mark yourself as "Me" in person edit to appear in all groups automatically and become the reference point on the age map.</p>
